$ echo x.[ba]
x.a x.b

  But

    $ echo x.{b,a}
    x.b x.a

  Also, beginners forget that x.[ba] must match something.

    $ mkdir /tmp/FOO; cd /tmp/FOO
    $ ls                  # nothing there
    $ touch x.[ba]
    $ ls
    x.[ba]                # one file!
    $ rm -f *
    $ touch x.{b,a}
    $ ls
    x.a x.b

  Brace expansion is text-substitution, while square brackets are a
  file-name-match operation.


